going to Yerevan in one week.. any recommendations? what to do during winter there?

Lore Roman spend one night in Tsakhkadzor itâ€™s beautiful in winter covered in snow. Ride Tsakhkadzor ropeway. Definitely visit Dilijan national park to get your nature fix. If you love wine, make sure to check out Saryan Steet in Yerevan. Itâ€™s wine lovers haven. It has many wine bars (â€œIn Vinoâ€ is my favorite). Also in Yerevan, check out Cascade and Republic Square (I like it at night). A few bars you can check out in Yerevan Kong Yerevan (awesome DJs), Dargett craft beer (brewery and weekend bands usually), EL Chillout (rooftop with nice views), Daboo cocktail bar (amazing cocktails!). Sites to visit: Geghard (4th century monastery). The Wings of Tatev (reversible aerial tramwayÂ on the Guinness World RecordÂ for the longest reversible aerial tramway). Also, Khor Virab (on a good day the views of Mt Ararat are breathtaking). Gyumri is the second largest city in Armenia after Yerevan. If you have time to visit Gyumri make sure to check out Aslamazyan sisters House Museum, work of Mariam and Eranuhi Aslamazyan. Think Armenian Frida kahlo x2. Cherkezi Dzor in Gyumri amazing fish restaurant. Anyway, do your own research since we all have different tastes and priorities. Happy travels! ğŸ˜„
